# Financial Tracker App — Build Checklist

## 1. Planning & Requirements
- [ ] Define target user (e.g., individual budgeters, young investors, FIRE-minded users)
- [ ] Decide monetization model (free, freemium, subscription) — affects feature gating
- [ ] List supported account types: checking/savings, credit cards, brokerage, crypto, loans
- [ ] Choose data source strategy: manual entry vs. bank-linking aggregator (Plaid, MX, Finicity, etc.)
- [ ] Define core currencies/locales to support (single currency MVP vs. multi-currency)
- [ ] Decide platform order: web first, mobile first, or parallel builds

## 2. Core Feature: Budgeting
- [ ] Income tracking (recurring + one-off)
- [ ] Expense categorization (auto-categorize via merchant/rules + manual override)
- [ ] Custom budget categories and sub-categories
- [ ] Monthly/weekly budget limits per category with rollover option
- [ ] Spending alerts (push/email when nearing or exceeding a limit)
- [ ] Recurring bill detection and reminders
- [ ] Cash flow view (income vs. expenses over time)

## 3. Core Feature: Savings
- [ ] Linked savings account balances (auto-sync or manual update)
- [ ] Sub-accounts / "buckets" for different savings purposes (emergency fund, vacation, etc.)
- [ ] Automatic savings rules (round-ups, % of income, scheduled transfers)
- [ ] Interest rate tracking and projected growth on savings balances
- [ ] Emergency fund target calculator (e.g., 3–6 months of expenses)

## 4. Core Feature: Investing
- [ ] Portfolio linking (brokerage accounts) or manual holdings entry
- [ ] Asset allocation breakdown (stocks, bonds, ETFs, crypto, real estate, cash)
- [ ] Performance tracking (returns by asset, account, and total portfolio)
- [ ] Benchmark comparison (e.g., vs. S&P 500)
- [ ] Dividend/interest income tracking
- [ ] Fee/expense ratio visibility
- [ ] Risk profile tagging per account or goal

## 5. Core Feature: Goal Setting & Forecasting
- [ ] Goal creation flow (name, target amount, target date, linked account/category)
- [ ] Goal types: savings goal, debt payoff, investment target, net worth milestone
- [ ] Required-contribution calculator (tells user $ amount needed per week/month to hit goal)
- [ ] "On track / behind / ahead" status indicator per goal, updated automatically
- [ ] Forecasting engine: project future balances using historical trends + assumed growth/contribution rates
- [ ] What-if simulator (e.g., "what if I save $50 more/month")
- [ ] Adjustable assumptions (inflation rate, expected investment return, income changes)
- [ ] Notifications when a goal falls off track, with suggested corrective action

## 6. Net Worth & Reporting
- [ ] Aggregated net worth dashboard (assets minus liabilities)
- [ ] Historical net worth trend chart
- [ ] Custom date-range reports (monthly, quarterly, yearly)
- [ ] Exportable reports (CSV/PDF) for taxes or personal records
- [ ] Debt tracking module (balances, interest rates, payoff timeline)

## 7. Mobile App
- [ ] Choose framework (native iOS/Android vs. cross-platform: React Native, Flutter)
- [ ] Biometric login (Face ID/fingerprint) + PIN fallback
- [ ] Push notifications for alerts, goal status, bill reminders
- [ ] Offline mode / cached data for viewing without connection
- [ ] Widget support (quick balance/goal glance on home screen)
- [ ] App store assets and submission requirements (Apple App Store, Google Play)

## 8. Web App
- [ ] Choose stack (e.g., React/Next.js frontend, shared backend/API with mobile)
- [ ] Responsive design for desktop and tablet
- [ ] Same core feature parity as mobile (budgeting, savings, investing, goals)
- [ ] CSV/spreadsheet import-export for power users
- [ ] Browser-based session security (auto-logout, 2FA)

## 9. Backend & Architecture
- [ ] Centralized API serving both mobile and web clients
- [ ] Database design for transactions, accounts, goals, users (normalized schema)
- [ ] Bank-data integration layer (if using Plaid/MX/etc.) with webhook handling for refreshes
- [ ] Background jobs for nightly balance sync, forecast recalculation, alert generation
- [ ] Caching layer for dashboard performance (Redis or similar)
- [ ] Scalable hosting plan (cloud provider, autoscaling for growth)

## 10. Personal Analytics Dashboard (Real-Time User Tracking)
*This is separate from the end-user-facing app — it's your own internal view into usage.*
- [ ] Define what to track: active users (DAU/MAU), signups, retention, feature usage, churn
- [ ] Event tracking instrumentation (e.g., Segment, Mixpanel, Amplitude, or custom event pipeline)
- [ ] Real-time dashboard (e.g., self-hosted Grafana/Metabase, or a custom admin panel)
- [ ] Downloadable reports (CSV/PDF export of user metrics on demand)
- [ ] User funnel tracking (signup → linked account → first goal → retained user)
- [ ] Alerting for anomalies (sudden drop in active users, spike in errors)
- [ ] Access control — this dashboard should be restricted to you/admins only, separate login from regular users

## 11. Security & Compliance
- [ ] Encrypt data at rest and in transit (TLS, AES-256)
- [ ] Secure storage of bank credentials (never store raw credentials if using an aggregator)
- [ ] Two-factor authentication for users
- [ ] Compliance review: data privacy laws (GDPR/CCPA as applicable), financial data regulations
- [ ] Regular security audits / penetration testing
- [ ] Clear privacy policy and terms of service
- [ ] Data deletion / account closure flow (right to be forgotten)

## 12. Testing
- [ ] Unit tests for forecasting/goal calculation logic (accuracy is critical here)
- [ ] Integration tests for bank-sync data pipeline
- [ ] Cross-device testing (iOS, Android, major browsers)
- [ ] Load testing for backend under concurrent user growth
- [ ] Beta testing group for real-world feedback before public launch

## 13. Launch & Post-Launch
- [ ] Onboarding flow (link first account, set first budget/goal in-app)
- [ ] In-app tutorial or tooltips for first-time users
- [ ] Feedback channel (in-app or email) for bug reports/feature requests
- [ ] Versioned release plan (MVP → v1.1 → v2 feature roadmap)
- [ ] Monitor the personal analytics dashboard post-launch to guide what to build next

---

**Suggested build order for an MVP:** Budgeting + savings tracking → goal setting with basic forecasting → investment tracking → mobile/web parity → personal analytics dashboard. This gets a usable product live before layering in real-time aggregator integrations and advanced forecasting.
